cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CE

This paper is primarily focused on the network infrastructure and communication technology, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses the integration of cross-domain networks, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The proposed evaluation metric and mathematical formulations suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the discussion of computational complexity and approximability suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category.
